    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white border-2 border-cyan-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Basement Waterproofing in Mississauga — Quick Facts</h2>
        <dl class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-8 gap-y-3 text-sm speakable">
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-slate-100 pb-2">
            <dt class="font-medium text-slate-600">Exterior waterproofing cost</dt>
            <dd class="font-bold text-slate-900">$150–$300 / linear ft</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-slate-100 pb-2">
            <dt class="font-medium text-slate-600">Interior drainage cost</dt>
            <dd class="font-bold text-slate-900">$80–$200 / linear ft</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-slate-100 pb-2">
            <dt class="font-medium text-slate-600">Average total project cost</dt>
            <dd class="font-bold text-slate-900">$15,000–$30,000</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-slate-100 pb-2">
            <dt class="font-medium text-slate-600">City rebate available</dt>
            <dd class="font-bold text-slate-900">Up to $3,400</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-slate-100 pb-2">
            <dt class="font-medium text-slate-600">Project timeline</dt>
            <dd class="font-bold text-slate-900">3–5 days (exterior)</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-slate-100 pb-2">
            <dt class="font-medium text-slate-600">Emergency response</dt>
            <dd class="font-bold text-slate-900">Under 45 minutes</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-slate-100 pb-2">
            <dt class="font-medium text-slate-600">Warranty</dt>
            <dd class="font-bold text-slate-900">25-year transferable</dd>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-slate-100 pb-2">
            <dt class="font-medium text-slate-600">Building permit required</dt>
            <dd class="font-bold text-slate-900">Yes (exterior excavation)</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
        <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-3">Prices as of 2026. Costs vary by home size, soil conditions, and scope of work.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Who Is the Best Basement Waterproofing Company in Mississauga?</h2>

        <p class="text-lg mb-6 speakable">
          <strong>DrySpace Waterproofing is Mississauga's most experienced basement waterproofing contractor, with 25+ years protecting over 500 homes across all neighborhoods from Port Credit to Malton.</strong> We specialize in Mississauga's unique challenges: Credit Valley clay soil that expands up to 70%, variable water tables from Lake Ontario and Credit River influences, and the rapid suburban development that has created diverse foundation challenges across different eras of construction.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Why Do Mississauga Homes Get Basement Water Problems?</h3>

        <p class="mb-4 speakable">
          <strong>Mississauga basements flood due to Credit Valley clay soil (30–70% clay content) that expands up to 70% when saturated, combined with a variable water table 1–4 metres below grade influenced by Lake Ontario and the Credit River.</strong>
        </p>

        <div class="bg-cyan-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
          <h4 class="font-bold mb-3">The Region's Unique Geological Challenges:</h4>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li>• <strong>Credit Valley Clay:</strong> 30-70% clay content causes extreme expansion/contraction</li>
            <li>• <strong>Variable Water Table:</strong> 1-4m depth fluctuates seasonally, highest near water bodies</li>
            <li>• <strong>Engineered Fill:</strong> Many subdivisions built on former farmland with imported soil</li>
            <li>• <strong>Lake Effect:</strong> Increased moisture and freeze-thaw cycles near Lake Ontario</li>
            <li>• <strong>Urban Heat Island:</strong> Rapid snow melt creates sudden water infiltration</li>
            <li>• <strong>Stormwater Management:</strong> Older neighborhoods lack modern drainage infrastructure</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What Waterproofing Methods Work Best for Mississauga Homes?</h3>

        <p class="mb-6 speakable">
          <strong>Exterior waterproofing ($150–$300/ft) is the most effective method for Mississauga's clay soil, while interior drainage systems ($80–$200/ft) are ideal for finished basements needing minimal disruption.</strong>
        </p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
          <div class="border p-4 rounded-lg">
            <h4 class="font-bold mb-2">Exterior Water Protection</h4>
            <p>Complete excavation to footing, membrane installation, and drainage systems. Ideal for Mississauga's clay soil conditions.</p>
            <ul class="text-sm mt-2 space-y-1">
              <li>✓ Excavation to footing level</li>
              <li>✓ Advanced membrane application</li>
              <li>✓ Drainage tile installation</li>
              <li>✓ Window well replacement</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="border p-4 rounded-lg">
            <h4 class="font-bold mb-2">Interior Drainage Systems</h4>
            <p>Interior drainage systems for finished basements and quick solutions without excavation.</p>
            <ul class="text-sm mt-2 space-y-1">
              <li>✓ Interior weeping tile</li>
              <li>✓ Sump pump installation</li>
              <li>✓ Vapor barriers</li>
              <li>✓ Crack injection</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="border p-4 rounded-lg">
            <h4 class="font-bold mb-2">Foundation Repair</h4>
            <p>Structural repairs for settlement and clay soil movement issues in Mississauga.</p>
            <ul class="text-sm mt-2 space-y-1">
              <li>✓ Crack repair</li>
              <li>✓ Bowing wall correction</li>
              <li>✓ Underpinning</li>
              <li>✓ Concrete restoration</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="border p-4 rounded-lg">
            <h4 class="font-bold mb-2">Emergency Services</h4>
            <p>24/7 emergency response to all Mississauga neighborhoods within 45 minutes.</p>
            <ul class="text-sm mt-2 space-y-1">
              <li>✓ Emergency pumping</li>
              <li>✓ Temporary moisture barriers</li>
              <li>✓ Flood cleanup</li>
              <li>✓ Insurance claims assistance</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Which Mississauga Neighborhoods Have the Worst Basement Flooding?</h3>

        <p class="mb-4 speakable">
          <strong>Meadowvale, Port Credit, and Streetsville experience the most basement flooding in Mississauga due to clay soil expansion, Credit River proximity, and aging 1970s-era drainage infrastructure.</strong>
        </p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-8">
          {mississaugaNeighborhoods.map(neighborhood => (
            <div class="bg-slate-50 p-4 rounded">
              {neighborhood.name === "Streetsville" ? (
                <h4 class="font-bold"><a href="/neighborhoods/streetsville" class="text-cyan-600 hover:underline">{neighborhood.name}</a></h4>
              ) : (
                <h4 class="font-bold">{neighborhood.name}</h4>
              )}
              <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">{neighborhood.projects} projects completed</p>
              <p class="text-xs mt-1">Common issues: {neighborhood.commonIssues}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Do You Need a Permit for Basement Waterproofing in Mississauga?</h3>

        <p class="mb-4 speakable">
          <strong>Yes, most exterior basement waterproofing projects in Mississauga require a building permit from the City of Mississauga Building Department for excavation exceeding 4 feet, plus separate plumbing permits for sump pumps and drainage.</strong> DrySpace is fully licensed and insured to work in Mississauga. We handle all permit applications with the City of Mississauga Building Department, including:
        </p>
        
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 space-y-2">
          <li>Building permits for exterior excavation exceeding 4 feet</li>
          <li>Plumbing permits for sump pump and drainage installations</li>
          <li>Site alteration permits for grading changes</li>
          <li>Heritage permits for properties in Streetsville and Port Credit heritage districts</li>
          <li>Region of Peel backwater valve installation permits</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-400 p-4 mb-8">
          <p class="font-bold">Important for Mississauga Homeowners:</p>
          <p>The City of Mississauga requires permits for most waterproofing work. Unpermitted work can result in
          fines and may not be covered by insurance. We handle all permits and inspections, ensuring your project
          meets all Mississauga codes and remains eligible for the $3,400 subsidy program.</p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What Rebates Are Available for Basement Waterproofing in Mississauga?</h3>

        <p class="mb-4 speakable">
          <strong>Mississauga homeowners can receive up to $3,400 through the Basement Flooding Protection Subsidy Program, plus additional Region of Peel rebates for backwater valves and sump pumps.</strong>
        </p>

        <div class="bg-cyan-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-8">
          <h4 class="font-bold mb-3">Available Rebates for Mississauga Residents:</h4>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li>
              <strong>Basement Flooding Protection Subsidy:</strong> Up to $3,400 for eligible foundation protection work
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Region of Peel Programs:</strong> Additional funding for backwater valves and sump pumps
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Insurance Premium Reductions:</strong> Up to 15% savings with certified waterproofing
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Property Tax Credits:</strong> Available for heritage properties in Streetsville and Port Credit
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 font-semibold">
            Our team handles all rebate applications and paperwork at no additional charge!
          </p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">The Mississauga Waterproofing Process</h3>
        
        <ol class="space-y-4 mb-8">
          <li class="flex">
            <span class="font-bold text-cyan-600 mr-3">1.</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Free Inspection:</strong> Our Mississauga-based inspector assesses your property,
              identifying specific issues related to Mississauga's soil and water conditions.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex">
            <span class="font-bold text-cyan-600 mr-3">2.</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Custom Solution:</strong> We design a waterproofing plan specific to your neighborhood's
              challenges and your home's construction era.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex">
            <span class="font-bold text-cyan-600 mr-3">3.</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Permit Application:</strong> We handle all City of Mississauga permit applications and
              drawings, ensuring code compliance.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex">
            <span class="font-bold text-cyan-600 mr-3">4.</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Professional Installation:</strong> Our certified crew completes the work, typically 
              within 3-5 days for exterior projects.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex">
            <span class="font-bold text-cyan-600 mr-3">5.</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Inspection & Warranty:</strong> City inspection approval and 25-year transferable 
              warranty registration.
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="flex">
            <span class="font-bold text-cyan-600 mr-3">6.</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Rebate Processing:</strong> We submit all documentation for your $3,400 subsidy claim.
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Why Choose DrySpace for Mississauga Foundation Waterproofing?</h3>
        
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-bold mb-2">Mississauga Expertise</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
              <li>✓ 15+ years serving Mississauga</li>
              <li>✓ 500+ Mississauga projects completed</li>
              <li>✓ Deep understanding of Credit Valley geology</li>
              <li>✓ Familiar with all neighborhood challenges</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-bold mb-2">Rapid Response</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
              <li>✓ 45-minute emergency response</li>
              <li>✓ Teams stationed across Mississauga</li>
              <li>✓ 24/7/365 availability</li>
              <li>✓ Same-day estimates</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-bold mb-2">Complete Service</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
              <li>✓ All permits handled</li>
              <li>✓ Rebate application assistance</li>
              <li>✓ Insurance claim support</li>
              <li>✓ Post-service monitoring</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-bold mb-2">Guaranteed Results</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
              <li>✓ 25-year transferable warranty</li>
              <li>✓ Licensed and insured</li>
              <li>✓ A+ BBB rating</li>
              <li>✓ Trusted since 1999</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Cost Calculator -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-8">
        How Much Does Basement Waterproofing Cost in Mississauga?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-center text-lg text-slate-600 mb-6 speakable">
        <strong>The average basement waterproofing project in Mississauga costs $15,000–$30,000 for a typical home, with exterior systems at $150–$300 per linear foot and interior systems at $80–$200 per linear foot.</strong> Use our calculator for a personalized estimate.
      </p>
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <CostCalculator client:load />
        <p class="text-center mt-4 text-sm text-slate-500">
          *Estimates include Mississauga-specific factors like clay soil conditions and permit fees
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Before/After Gallery -->
  <section id="gallery" class="py-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-8">
        Recent Mississauga Projects
      </h2>
      <BeforeAfterGallery />
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mt-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center">
          <img src="/images/port-credit-project.webp" alt="Port Credit foundation protection" class="rounded-lg mb-2" width="400" height="300" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
          <p class="font-semibold">Port Credit Heritage Home</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Complete exterior protection system</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <img src="/images/meadowvale-project.webp" alt="Meadowvale foundation repair" class="rounded-lg mb-2" width="400" height="300" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
          <p class="font-semibold">Meadowvale Clay Soil Solution</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Foundation stabilization & drainage</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <img src="/images/streetsville-project.webp" alt="Streetsville basement" class="rounded-lg mb-2" width="400" height="300" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
          <p class="font-semibold">Streetsville Flood Recovery</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-slate-500">Emergency response & permanent fix</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Social Proof -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 text-center max-w-2xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Trusted by Mississauga Homeowners</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 mb-6">
        We've completed over 500 basement waterproofing projects across Mississauga — from Port Credit heritage homes to Meadowvale clay soil solutions.
      </p>
